import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='yield', data=data)
    median_yield = sm.stats.DescrStatsW(data['yield']).mean
    ax.axvline(median_yield, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median Yield: {median_yield:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the average yield of barley across all sites and years?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='yield', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend in yield over time?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    mean_yield_by_site = data.groupby('site')['yield'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='site', y='yield', data=mean_yield_by_site)
    plt.title('How does the yield vary across different sites?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```
